# Astro pages and styling

## Layouts

- Wrap pages in `BaseLayout` so `_base.scss` chrome (grid, scanlines, vignette) applies automatically.
- Global styles: `src/styles/main.scss` imports partials in order — add new partials there with `@use "name";`.

## Design system

- Tokens: `_variables.scss` (`--bg`, `--surface-*`, `--text-*`, `--brand`, `--accent-*`)
- HUD utilities: `_hacker.scss` — `.label-mono`, `.heading-bracket`, `.hud-corners`, `.telemetry-rail`, `.accent-block`, `.terminal-prefix`, `.status-block`
- Fonts: Source Sans 3 (body), Source Serif 4 (display), Source Code Pro (mono)

## Component styles

- Scoped `<style>` in `.astro` is fine for small component-specific tweaks.
- Client scripts: `<script>` in `.astro` components, or `public/assets/js/` for larger bundles.
